content: This is one of the best puzzle games I've ever played. The concept is very simple, but allows for some real complex, head-scratching levels. At the same time, the challenge never feels unfair. The pacing of difficulty is so well thought out that it keeps you playing for a while, and the ethereal & unnerving sound design turn an already great game into a full-on experience. This is what mobile games should strive to be.
Great logical puzzler with even better style.

Nice game

you're given a bunch of small triangle pieces that have colored tips and your job is to match them up with other triangles so that they form one larger piece. Controls are simple, tapping rotates the triangle and tapping inside or outside of the triangle zooms you in or out respectively. It's very simple but very engaging for puzzle fans. I love the look but sometimes the colors of the font and triangles can clash. I don't think there's any music but the ambient sounds are great, stuff like crickets or rainfall or white noise. All the puzzles feel fair so when I get suck I take a break and come back to tackle the puzzle again. No IAPs or ads either, what a gem of a game!
